cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about self-supervised video representation learning using a new task called Space-Time Cubic Puzzles. The task involves arranging permuted 3D spatio-temporal crops, which requires the network to learn both spatial appearance and temporal relation of video frames. This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual representation learning for videos. It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it involves training a neural network using a self-supervised task. Additionally, it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with video data. It may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories as it involves developing a new self-supervised task and training a neural network for representation learning.
